Consumer complaint narrative:
XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Apt XXXX, XXXX, TX XXXX XXXX : XX/XX/XXXX TransUnion Consumer Solutions XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, PA XXXX XXXX : XXXX Re : Security Freeze Request Dear Sir/Madam, I, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Social Security XXXX XXXX, a resident of XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXXXXXX XXXX XXXX  XXXX, TX XXXX, submit this affidavit to request a security freeze on my credit report. Pursuant to my rights under applicable federal and state laws, including but not limited to the Fair Credit Reporting Act and any other relevant regulations, I hereby formally request that a Security Freeze be placed on my credit file immediately. 
Affidavit : Applicant Identification : Full Name : XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Social Security Number : XXXX Date of Birth : XX/XX/XXXX Current Address : XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Apt XXXX, XXXX XXXX TX XXXX XXXX XXXX Request : o I request that a security freeze be placed on my credit report to prevent unauthorized third-party access, except for those legally authorized or with my explicit consent. 
o This freeze should remain in place until I personally request its removal in writing, in compliance with applicable legal requirements. 
Attached Documentation : I have attached the following documents to verify my identity and process my request : o A copy of my drivers license or government-issued ID. 
o A copy of a recent utility bill or bank statement confirming my current address. 
o A copy of my Social Security Number. 
Affirmation : I declare under penalty of perjury that the information provided in this affidavit is true and correct to the best of my knowledge. This request is made in good faith to protect my credit information. 
Confirmation Request : I hereby request written confirmation of the receipt and implementation of this security freeze request. I appreciate your prompt attention to this matter. 
Sincerely, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX

Consumer complaint narrative:
Subject : Dispute of Unauthorized Hard Inquiries on Credit Report XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, Fl XXXX XX/XX/XXXX Social Security XXXX XX/XX/XXXX Consumer Financial Protection Bureau XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, IA XXXX To Whom It May Concern, I am writing to formally dispute unauthorized hard inquiries that have appeared on my credit report. I did not authorize these inquiries, and they are negatively impacting my credit score. Despite previous attempts to resolve this matter with the credit bureaus, these inquiries remain on my report. 

The disputed hard inquiries are as follows : XXXX. XXXXXXXX XXXX XXXX XXXXXXXX Date of Inquiry : XX/XX/XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Issue : I did not apply for credit with this company, and I did not authorize this inquiry. 

XXXX. XXXX XXXX XXXX Date of Inquiry : XX/XX/XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, Florida XXXX Issue : I have no relationship with this creditor and never consented to this inquiry. 

XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Hard Inquiries ) [ 15 U.S. Code 1602p ] Under the Fair Credit Reporting Act ( FCRA ), hard inquiries require my explicit authorization. Since I did not authorize these inquiries, I request their immediate removal from my credit file. 

I have previously contacted the credit bureaus regarding this matter but have not received a satisfactory resolution. As the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau has taken action against credit bureaus for inadequate dispute handling, I am now escalating my complaint to your office for investigation and enforcement. 

Enclosed are copies of my credit report with the unauthorized inquiries highlighted, as well as any supporting documents. I kindly request that you take action to have these inquiries removed and ensure that the credit bureaus comply with federal regulations. 

Please acknowledge receipt of this dispute and inform me of any further steps required. I appreciate your prompt attention to this matter. 

Sincerely, XXXX XXXX
Company public response: Company has responded to the consumer and the CFPB and chooses not to provide a public response
